article.headline: Gardner-Webb 95, Liberty 90
article.story: BOILING SPRINGS, N.C. -- Takayo Siddle hit shots to send the game into overtime, force a second extra frame and seal Gardner-Webb's 95-90 win over Liberty on Wednesday night. Siddle hit a 3-pointer with 10 seconds left in regulation to tie the score at 72-all, which held up to force overtime. Then, with the Runnin' Bulldogs (11-11, 7-5 Big South Conference) down 80-76 in the first overtime, Siddle took over once again. The guard nailed a layup with 5 seconds left, stole Liberty's inbounds pass and hit a jumper to tie the score with 1 second left, sending the game into a second overtime. In a final OT frame that was tight early, Siddle hit four free throws in the final minute to seal Gardner-Webb's win. Siddle finished with a career-high 18 points to lead Gardner-Webb. Kyle Ohman scored 38 points for the Flames (16-8, 7-5), and also grabbed 10 boards.
